# Numen UI Design Track тАФ rules for this worktree

This worktree (`virtuna-numen-ui`, branch `design/ui-system`) is the **UI design track**.
It runs in PARALLEL with an engine/backend rework happening in a separate worktree
(`virtuna-engine-rework`, branch `rework/engine-core`). Stay in your lane to avoid conflicts.

## 1. Design system тАФ trust ONE source
- The **only** authoritative design references are `src/app/globals.css` (the `@theme` token
  block) and `docs/DESIGN-SYSTEM.md`. Read `docs/DESIGN-SYSTEM.md` before any visual work.
- **IGNORE these тАФ they are STALE** (they describe the retired Raycast/coral/glass system):
  `CLAUDE.md` "Raycast Design Language Rules" section, `BRAND-BIBLE.md`, `docs/tokens.md`,
  `docs/components.md`, `docs/design-specs.json`, `docs/usage-guidelines.md`,
  `docs/motion-guidelines.md`, `docs/brand/`.
- Current system = **flat-warm charcoal + cream text + terracotta accent + matte**:
  - bg `#262624` (`--color-background`), cream text `#ece7de` (`--cream-primary`) тАФ **never `#fff`**
  - accent terracotta `#d97757` (`--color-accent`) тАФ **never `#FF7F50`**
  - borders 6% (`rgba(255,255,255,0.06)`), hover 10%
  - **matte only**: no glass gradients, no glow, no white inset-shine. Flat + border + (rarely) `--shadow-float`.
  - Inter for all chrome; Newsreader serif **only** for voice-moments (greeting/hero).
  - radius 4/6/8/12/16/20/24 тАФ cards 12, inputs/buttons 8.
- **Always consume tokens, never hardcode hex.** No `#FF7F50`, `#07080a`, `#18191a`, `#fff`.
- Keep `src/components/reading/__tests__/reskin-matte.test.ts` GREEN (guards against coral/glass).

## 2. File ownership тАФ DO NOT cross
- тЬЕ **You own:** `src/components/**`, page-level styling/layout in `src/app/(app)/**` (NON-api),
  `src/app/globals.css`, design tokens, `src/types/design-tokens.ts`.
- тЫФ **Do NOT touch (engine track owns these):** `src/lib/**`, `src/app/api/**`, runners,
  engine, `supabase/**`, prompt/KC files. If a UI change seems to need a backend change,
  STOP and flag it тАФ don't edit backend here.

## 3. Coupled surfaces тАФ visual-only, don't change contracts
`AudienceLens`, the composer, and the thread skill-cards are being reworked on the engine side
(their data shape/props may change). For these you MAY restyle/relayout, but **do NOT change the
props/data contracts** they consume or the block schemas. Structural changes to these wait for
the engine rework тАФ coordinate first.

## 4. Conflict hygiene
- Rebase onto `origin/main` frequently (`git fetch origin && git rebase origin/main`).
- Keep PRs small and per-surface; merge often to minimize drift.
- Commit format `type(surface): description`. Atomic commits.

## 5. Verify before done
- `npm run lint` + typecheck clean.
- Visual check in the browser (or screenshot) for any surface you change.
- Don't say "should work" тАФ show it.
